<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Voice capabilities</h2>
	<ul class="features-grid">
		<li class="feature">
			<h3>Origination and termination</h3>
			<p>Run inbound and outbound voice through VoiceTel with published rate keys, routing controls, and carrier-support escalation paths.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<h3>VoiceML call control</h3>
			<p>Answer, route, record, gather, dial, queue, conference, redirect, stream, and transcribe calls using XML-based voice markup.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<h3>Signed webhooks</h3>
			<p>Status, recording, gather, dial, conference, AMD, and action callbacks use signed webhook delivery for request verification.</p>
		</li>
		<li class="feature">
			<h3>Bring your own media vendors</h3>
			<p>Use your preferred speech-to-text, text-to-speech, and recording storage providers where supported; VoiceTel does not hide third-party provider costs inside vague platform claims.</p>
		</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
